The paper proposes a method for optimizing neural network structures during training, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on deep neural networks and their architectures, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed method to image classification tasks using datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, and CIFAR-100, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions optimizing the connections between units, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a probabilistic modeling approach, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
